<section id="privacy" class="band">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="head">
      <p>Privacy</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid">
      <h2>Your data lives on your device, not ours.</h2>
      <div class="text">
        <p>There's no account, no sign-up, and no Pillot server holding your information. Your medications, schedules, and history live on your device. If you use iCloud Backup, they are included in your own encrypted Apple backup, and Pillot never receives them.</p>
        <p>The one exception: when you scan a label, that photo travels over an encrypted connection to an AI reader, Anthropic's Claude, just long enough to turn it into your digital label. It is never used to train AI, Anthropic deletes it under their commercial retention policy, and our own server keeps nothing.</p>
        <p>Prescription labels usually show your name, so the photo you send may include it. Pillot never extracts your name from a label, never stores it, and never uses it for anything.</p>
        <p class="strong">That's the whole story. No analytics, no trackers, no data to sell, because we don't have any to begin with.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .band {
    background: var(--slate);
    color: var(--paper);
    margin-top: 52px;
    padding-block: 40px 48px;
  }

  .head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--slate-line);
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 26px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.4fr;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3.4vw, 34px);
    max-width: 15ch;
    color: var(--terracotta);
  }

  .text p {
    color: var(--slate-text);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .text p.strong {
    color: var(--paper);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 18px;
    }

    h2 {
      max-width: none;
    }
  }
</style>
